pr_review_comment_body:
Oh I see. Yes, it is unreachable indeed. It should not be removed though. 
Please change it to:

```
if isinstance(c_code, bool):
    c_code = textwrap.dedent(
        """
        #include <unistd.h>
        int main() {
            pause();
            return 1;
        }
        """)

assert isinstance(c_code, str), c_code
```

I see here why you used `this.$parent.$emit` in the perseus renderer.

I think more appropriate would be for perseus to say `this.$emit` and then in the html above you can do:

```html
<slot
  v-if="ready"
  @checkanswer="somemethod"
  @takehint="somemethod"
  @passexercise="somemethod"
></slot>
```

Here is the code, I tried:

class GuidMixin(object):
    def __init__(self):
        self.guid = generate_uuid()

class Subclass(GuidMixin):

    def printx(self):
        print self.guid

if __name__ == "__main__":
    a = Subclass()
    b = Subclass()

    print a.guid
    a.printx()

    print b.guid
    b.printx()

Could you add a comment that explains why we're using location.replace here, i.e. to ensure that navigating back doesn't result in a loop?  Also maybe note that the call to tf_storage.setString() in this case will supersede the one that will be invoked by _selectedDashboardChanged() once we update _selectedDashboard below.

Also, this line is a bit long, can you wrap it e.g. to

```js
tf_storage.setString(
  tf_storage.TAB,
  selectedDashboard,
  /*useLocalStorage=*/false,
  /*useLocationReplace=*/true);
```
